Description: fix 64-bit portability issues
 - Use uint32_t for the LCG seed (was unsigned long: 32-bit on Windows LLP64,
   64-bit on Linux LP64) and matching 32-bit unsigned constants, so the random
   sequence is deterministic and correct on all platforms.
 - Replace %u with %zu for size_t arguments to ERR/LOG, and %d for int
   arguments that were mistakenly passed to %u.
 - Use size_t loop variables when iterating over size_t-returning getCount()
   / .size(), eliminating signed/unsigned width mismatches.
 - Use size_t for ObjLoader::range_t members (was int) and for range_start,
   silencing implicit-narrowing conversions from size_t.
 - Add explicit cast for ftell() → size_t assignment.
